title: Alice's Adventures in Wonderland by Lewis Carroll (Book Summary) - Minute Book Report

json.text: This is a story about a girl named Alice who falls down a rabbit hole while chasing a White
Rabbit. After falling for quite some time, she lands softly in a great hall and begins
looking for a way out. She sees a small door, but can’t fit through it. She drinks from
a bottle labeled “Drink Me” and shrinks. However, she’s too small to open the door
with a key and so she eats some cake to grow tall. She begins to cry, but after holding
a fan, she shrinks back down and finds herself in water.
The water disappears and Alice is ordered by the White Rabbit to fetch a fan and some
gloves from his house. She enters the White Rabbit’s house and drinks from a bottle,
which makes her grow, resulting in her being stuck in the house. The White Rabbit gets
scared and tries to get her out. Alice eats more cake and shrinks back down.
Alice encounters a caterpillar who is smoking a hookah. They talk and then she enters a
house with a woman who is nursing a baby. The woman leaves the baby alone with Alice.
The baby transforms into a pig and Alice lets it go in the wild.
Alice then encounters a Cheshire Cat in the woods, who directs her to the March Hare’s
house for a tea party. At the tea party, Alice meets the March Hare, Mad Hatter, and Dormouse.
After talking with them over tea, she leaves and enters the Queen of Hearts’ garden.
She meets the Queen of Hearts and they play a game of croquet with flamingoes and hedgehogs,
while the Queen threatens her subjects with beheadings.
The Cheshire Cat appears and the Queen orders a beheading of the cat, but the cat can't
be beheaded since the cat can make his body disappear.
Alice appears at a hearing that is held by the King and Queen of Hearts over who had
stolen a missing tart. After a few witnesses, Alice is called to the stand and begins to
grow larger and larger.
In the end, Alice wakes up from her experience in Wonderland and her sister reflects on a
similar experience she had as a little girl.
